INSERT INTO `activitydb_projectagreement` VALUES (4,NULL,'Participatory Market Mapping Workshop-almond value chain','32550A001','','Participatory Market Mapping Workshop-almond value chain','','8500','721','',0,'','What is the anticipated effect or impact of this project?:  (not outputs and not full description) \r\n1.	The stakeholders in the market system/ value chain will be able to identify gaps in the entire value chains and look for appropriate solutions either through engaging with themselves in small groups or seeking support from relevant other stakeholders.\r\n2.	The stakeholders engaged in the chain will start to find meaning in taking the issues confronting the value chain/market system and form a forum to engage in the longer-term to discuss progress and challenges. \r\n','2014-12-08 08:00:00','2014-12-15 08:00:00','','','','','',333.60,333.60,3,NULL,'2015-05-05 07:00:00',NULL,'2015-05-06 07:00:00',NULL,'2015-05-06 07:00:00','approved',NULL,'','','','1-	Identification of the key and influential stakeholders\r\n2-	Conducting the workshop\r\n3-	Presenting the Preliminary Market Map\r\n4-	Summarising the list of problems/gaps in the market system\r\n5-	List the potential solutions as proposed by the stakeholder\r\n6-	Propose formation of the stakeholder forum  \r\n','','','2015-12-02 06:03:21','2015-12-02 06:03:21',NULL,NULL,NULL,8,8,8,8,67,3,3,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(228,NULL,'Linkage and Planning Training to DDAs & CDCs ','32550A066','','5.1.1 Building Sub-national governance linkages','','8500','741','',0,'',' The anticipated outcomes and impacts of this project would be explained as following: \r\nCommunication and linkages of community based institutions with relevant departments will be improved which helps in resolving issues.\r\nThe participants would be able to develop community development plans.\r\nAfter receiving this training the participants would be able expand the knowledge to members of other relevant institutions to make them able to serve their communities for stable and prosperous nation.','2015-06-07 07:00:00','2015-06-18 07:00:00','','','','','',2536.00,2536.00,NULL,'2015-06-04 07:00:00','2015-11-11 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Based on SAGAL work plan this training program is planned as TOT and the participants would be expected to deliver the same type of trainings to be expanded to the rest of local governance institutions. This 2 days training  will cover both theoretical and practical aspects of the issues emerged from the needs assessment done during conducted workshop with these mentioned institutions, practical sessions of learning by participation and group discussion will be facilitated during the training and the topics have been scheduled as following:\r\nDay1: Linkage training- one day\r\nDay2: Planning training- one day\r\nSAGAL Hilmand team will facilitate the coordination meetings with DDAs, IDLG, appointed trainer and with other line departments, Similarly other tasks including but not limited to collecting of beneficiaries list, writing of PA+BOQ, financial documents and providing the required stuffs, venue selection and invitation of participants will be carried out by SAGAL team.','','','2015-12-09 05:28:45','2015-12-09 05:28:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,34,NULL,NULL,7,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55','2015-06-04',139480.00,139480.00,'',NULL),(5,NULL,'Participatory Market Mapping Workshop-Cumin value chain','32550A002','','Participatory Market Mapping Workshop-Cumin value chain','','8500','721','',0,'','What is the anticipated effect or impact of this project?:  (not outputs and not full description) \r\n1.	The stakeholders in the market system/ value chain will be able to identify gaps in the entire value chains and look for appropriate solutions either through engaging with themselves in small groups or seeking support from relevant other stakeholders.\r\n2.	The stakeholders engaged in the chain will start to find meaning in taking the issues confronting the value chain/market system and form a forum to engage in the longer-term to discuss progress and challenges. \r\n','2014-12-10 08:00:00','2014-12-15 08:00:00','','','','','',333.60,333.60,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,'','','','1-	Identification of the key and influential stakeholders\r\n2-	Conducting the workshop\r\n3-	Presenting the Preliminary Market Map\r\n4-	Summarising the list of problems/gaps in the market system\r\n5-	List the potential solutions as proposed by the stakeholder\r\n6-	Propose formation of the stakeholder forum  \r\n','','','2015-12-06 09:03:02','2015-12-06 09:03:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,8,67,3,3,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(255,NULL,'Financial Management and Record Keeping Training for 10 WUA','91115A004','','2.2 Mentoring in internal financial management system, 2.3:Follow up on financial management system','','8500/8530','91115L012','',0,'','As a result of delivering  financial management training the technical knowledge of the water users associations’ board members will be increased, financial management system will be promoted and administered within the command area of WUA , effective and efficient use of funds ensured, trust and confidence created and strengthened among the members, ensure readiness to give explanation about the financial situation, and  assisted maintenance of economic viability and long term existence.','2016-01-05 08:00:00','2016-04-30 07:00:00','','','','','',1491.53,1341.53,4,'2015-12-28 08:00:00','2015-12-28 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Since 2007, Mercy Corps (MC) through EC founded Kunduz integrated Water Initiative KIWI-1 and KIWI-2 programs has helped farmers to establish and strengthen 10 Water Users’ Associations (WUA) and 36 Water Users’ Groups (WUG).\r\nMC helped farmers to establish WUA, supported them to rehabilitate and construct small-scale irrigation infrastructures, improved their governance through training in water management, legal issues and good governance, and adopting new, more water efficient, agriculture and irrigation practices and supported them to become the first WUAs in Afghanistan to be registered. In order to sustain this achievement in the development of social water management through WUA under the Water Law( 2009), there are challenges that require multi-year funding streams to overcome.\r\n\r\nIn general, all the water user associations do not have financial management system to keep the record of incomes that they received from different sources particularly  from irrigation service fee as well as they don’t keep the record of  expenses that carried out for the implementation of operation and maintenance activities plan. \r\nWhenever, the WUA granted or donated any fund or collect  the money from the water users for doing some small scale project and rehabilitate the irrigation structure the fund/money is being spent by the authorized bodies but none of the records are being kept as a prove documents.besides, the technical capacity of the WUAs’ board members are much low, unfamiliar with the financial and record keeping forms/books, neither they keep the record of general financial activities, minutes of all meetings, nor they register bargains, contracts,and proper filing system. due to the mentioned challenges/problem the accountability and transparency of financial issues are not exist, financial reports are not prepared and presented to the members of WUA in general assembly.\r\nAs the Water Users’ Association (WUA) is the organization generated by water-users (farmers and other water users) that renders certain services in  operating and maintaining irrigation and drainage systems. It is the most economic and effective form of the organization for providing the water-users with such services. For the given systems to be operated and maintained, the WUA should develop budgets, estimates, and determine payment for irrigational services and collect payment for the services rendered, that is to keep financial management.\r\n\r\nIn order to address the above said challenges and  increase the technical  knowledge, build the capacity of the  WUAs, it is proposed to facilitate financial management and record keeping  training which enable the WUAs to keep the proper records of financial activities register all the assets, prepare financial reports and present the financial reports in the general Assembly.  such trainings   should be conducted for  10 existing WUAs, in Kunduz, Chardara, Qalai Zal and Alia bad districts of Kunduz province and Baghlan Jadid, Pole Khumri and Nuhreen districts of Baghlan province. \r\n\r\nIt is worth mentioning that after delivering this training four follow up meetings will be conducted individually with each of the WUA ( Head, Secretory & Treasurer) one follow up meeting will be held in January,2016 after training delivery and the second, third and fourth will be held in order in February, ','','','2015-11-30 10:36:07','2015-11-30 10:36:08',NULL,NULL,NULL,26,NULL,NULL,10,168,3,NULL,10,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','60 AFN','2015-12-28',80491.00,89491.80,'',NULL),(6,NULL,'TOT- SAGAL Orientation and Technical Training - Almond & Cumin - DAIL extension department','32550A003','','TOT- SAGAL Orientation and Technical Training - Almond & Cumin - DAIL extension department','','8500','712','',0,'','DAIL extension department will fully understand about SAGAL program’s objectives and activities, strong coordination will be established, DAIL extension department will be able to train farmers on district levels and MCA- SAGAL will facilitate those trainings in SAGAL targeted districts.  Similarly DAIL’s extension, forestry, plant protection and cooperative departments will be able to deliver the services directly to the farmers in our selected Almond and Cumin value chains. ','2014-12-24 08:00:00','2015-01-05 08:00:00','','','','','',535.00,535.00,3,'2014-12-17 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Strengthening the institutional capacity of DAIL is the key activity based on SAGAL work plan. SAGAL will organize 3days training to DAIL staff in Trinkot and Dehrawod district of Urozgan. This training will include the following 1-	Preparation of training curriculum (Pashto) by Agriculture expert.\r\n2-	Total 3 days training for 10 staff members of DAIL Trinkot and Dehrawod. \r\n3-	One day training on SAGAL orientation.\r\n4-	Two days technical training in almond and cumin value chains,\r\n5-	M&E of the training will be continued during the training sessions,\r\n6-	Pre and post training evaluation will be conducted using MCA standard evaluation forms,\r\n7-	SAGAL Team will write the final training report','','','2015-11-28 04:46:12','2015-11-28 04:46:12',NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,8,67,3,3,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(7,NULL,'Timber Exposure Visit for members of Helmand Nursery Growers Association','32550َA046','','2.2.4 Exposure to markets for Associations','','8500','726','',0,'','After the exposure visit the nursery growers will grow nurseries of improved poplar varieties and will propagate saplings/ cuttings to farmers across the target districts, this will increase income return to the nursery growers.  Commercial timber cultivation as a potential licit crop might emerge as an alternative source of income generation to improve the economic status of farmers.\r\n','0014-12-02 08:00:00','0014-12-10 08:00:00','','','','','',1930.00,1930.00,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-13 07:00:00',NULL,'2015-05-13 07:00:00',NULL,'2015-11-16 08:00:00','','2015-11-17 08:00:00','','','','Strengthening the institutional capacity of NGA members is the key activity based on SAGAL work plan. \r\nSAGAL will organize a 3days exposure visit for NGA members to Guldara district of Kabul, the visit will make them able to transfer the new varieties of timbers to Helmand province. Beneficiary nursery growers will introduce the new verities in Helmand and after showing good results will expand across the target districts.\r\nThis visit will include the following activities; \r\n1.	Identifying of NGA and obtaining of members list.\r\n2.	Coordination with NGA to Introduce 4 members for exposure visit.\r\n3.	Planning for visit arrangement.\r\n4.	Providing of financial documents.\r\n5.	Conducting the visit.\r\n6.	Feedback from participants for evaluation of exposure visit.\r\n7.	Writing of final report.\r\n','','','2015-12-08 05:10:15','2015-12-08 05:10:15',NULL,NULL,NULL,6,NULL,34,7,67,3,5,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(232,NULL,'Second Market Forum Meeting – Grapes Market System','32550A070','','2.1.1: Value Chain Analysis','','8500','721','',0,'','The stakeholders in the market system/ value chain will be able to identify gaps in the entire value chains and look for appropriate solutions either through engaging with themselves in small groups or seeking support from relevant other stakeholders.\r\nThe stakeholders engaged in the chain will start to find meaning in taking the issues confronting the value chain/market system and form a forum to engage in the longer-term to discuss progress and challenges.','2015-07-09 07:00:00','2015-07-16 07:00:00','','','','','',397.00,397.00,NULL,'2015-07-07 07:00:00','2015-11-11 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Hilmand SAGAL conducted the first Market Forum Meeting in April-2015, so based on the stakeholders list provided at startup phase of this project the Key stakeholders relevant to the grapes market-chain will be invited to participate in the second market forum meeting, any required facilities such as stationery, transportation cost, incentives, meeting venue with all requirements would be provided as well, the market forum meeting  would be facilitated by Hilmand SAGAL team directly, the previous information such as noted gapes, issues, problems, challenges and action points would be showed and shared with all participants during this meeting, finally all of the presented new information and action points would be noted and listed as well  for coming plan.','','','2015-12-09 09:12:33','2015-12-09 09:12:33',NULL,NULL,NULL,34,NULL,NULL,7,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55','2015-07-07',21835.00,21835.00,'',NULL),(8,NULL,'Participatory Market Mapping Workshop- Watermelon Market System','32550A049','','2.1.1: Value Chain Analysis','','8500','','',0,'','What is the anticipated effect or impact of this project?:  (not outputs and not full description) \r\n1.	The stakeholders in the market system/ value chain will be able to identify gaps in the entire value chains and look for appropriate solutions either through engaging with themselves in small groups or seeking support from relevant other stakeholders.\r\n2.	The stakeholders engaged in the chain will start to find meaning in taking the issues confronting the value chain/market system and form a forum to engage in the longer-term to discuss progress and challenges\r\n','2014-12-08 08:00:00','2014-12-15 08:00:00','','','','','',433.00,433.00,NULL,'2014-12-03 08:00:00','2015-05-13 07:00:00',NULL,'2015-05-13 07:00:00',NULL,'2015-11-17 08:00:00','approved','2015-11-17 08:00:00','','','','1-	Identification of the key and influential stakeholders\r\n2-	Conducting the workshop\r\n3-	Presenting the Preliminary Market Map\r\n4-	Summarising the list of problems/gaps in the market system\r\n5-	List the potential solutions as proposed by the stakeholders\r\n6-	Propose formation of the stakeholder forum  \r\n','','','2015-11-17 09:37:27','2015-11-17 09:37:27',98,98,NULL,6,NULL,34,7,67,3,5,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(214,NULL,'Workshop for expanding Input Suppliers services coverage','32550A051','','1.2.2 Expand input supplier service coverage','','8500','714','',0,'','Big input Suppliers would present their professional services, input supplies and new technologies to small input suppliers in our target districts. Small input suppliers could have faster, easiest and cheaper access to their required input supplies which can benefit their beneficiary farmers and ultimately results in higher productivity.\r\nBig input suppliers will expand the range of their supply chain through small retailers to farmer community and this network could improve the production both qualitatively and quantitatively.','2015-01-20 08:00:00','2015-01-31 08:00:00','','','','','',546.00,546.00,NULL,'2015-01-14 08:00:00','2015-11-09 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Coordination Meetings with Bost Input Suppliers’ Association\r\nPreparing of all the required documents(Financial and Administrative Documents) \r\nFollowing arrangement of big retailer’s presentations.\r\nConducting of (Workshop for Expanding Input Supplier Service Coverage).\r\nCollection of the required documents using in the activity report such as pictures, payments sheets and etc.\r\nFinal completion report. ','','','2015-12-08 06:04:51','2015-12-08 06:04:51',NULL,NULL,NULL,34,NULL,NULL,7,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55','2015-01-14',30030.00,30030.00,'',NULL),(9,NULL,'TOT- Pesticide & Herbicides training - Input suppliers','32550A004','','TOT- Pesticide & Herbicides training - Input suppliers','','8500','713','',0,'','The input supplier will understand about SAGAL program objectives and activities, strong coordination will be established, bigger input supplier will be able to train smaller input supplier on district levels and MCA- SAGAL will facilitate those trainings in SAGAL targeted areas, smaller input suppliers will be able to link the farmers to themselves and other local and national traders.','2015-01-05 08:00:00','2015-01-15 08:00:00','','','','','',1200.00,1200.00,NULL,'2014-12-30 08:00:00','2014-12-30 08:00:00',NULL,'2014-12-30 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,'','','','Support input supplier is the key activity based on SAGAL work plan. SAGAL will organize 2days training to input suppliers which includes the following activities; \r\n1.	Preparation of training curriculum (Pashto) by appointed person.\r\n2.	Fifteen input suppliers will be selected as trainees and a potential one as trainer.   \r\n3.	The trainer will provide two days theoretical and practical training to 15 input suppliers.\r\n4.	All 11 standard forms will be filled by program team from starting up to the end of project.\r\n5.	Monitoring for quality assurance will be continued during the training sessions,\r\n6.	Pre and post training evaluation will be conducted using MCA standard evaluation forms,\r\n7.	SAGAL Team will write the final training report.','','','2015-12-06 09:16:06','2015-12-06 09:16:06',NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,8,67,3,3,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(281,NULL,'Market forum meeting- almond and cumin in Tarin Kot and Dihrawud districts','32550A019','','Value Chain Analysis','','8500','721','',0,'','Stake holders of selected value chain will share relevant gap of almond and cumin and they will find the easiest solution for it, they will be able to identify gaps in the entire value chains and look for appropriate solutions either through engaging with themselves in small groups or seeking support from relevant other stakeholders.\r\nThis forum meeting will link entire market actors and stake holders of almond and cumin to each other. \r\n','2015-05-20 07:00:00','2015-06-10 07:00:00','','','','','',289.00,289.00,3,'2015-05-17 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,'','','','Oruzgan SAGAL team will conduct 2 days Multi stake holders’ forum meeting for 30 various stake holders. First day will be market forum meeting of almond and second day will be market forum meeting of Cumin.\r\nRepresentatives of Farmers Association, traders association and input supplier association coordination with line department will introduce appropriate market actors to Multi stake holders form meeting. \r\nSAGAL team will manage meeting room, prepare all meeting materials, inaugurate meeting and assist with participant during grouping works and note suggestion, problems and challenge of participants during meeting.  \r\nAll activities related to finance, procurement and logistics will be properly planned, documented and approved, and the BOQ for this meeting is annexed to this PA.  This meeting will cover all gaps and challenges of almond& cumin, analysis and solution of entire gaps in selected value chain.\r\n','','','2015-11-30 03:08:45','2015-11-30 03:08:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(12,NULL,'Formation and Registration-Association','32550A005','','Formation and Registration-Association','','8500','723','',0,'','Mercy Corps/SAGAL is committed, to support the different stakeholders and establish several association for making of good social and work frame for the improvement of agriculture and market system in future. This activity will has the following impacts:\r\n1.	Whenever the associations registered the stakeholders will be able to utilize their own capacity and make a sustainable market system for agriculture products.\r\n2.	The stakeholders will be linked to line sectors and market players, and make these associations self-sustainable.\r\n','2015-02-01 08:00:00','2015-05-31 07:00:00','','','','','',1200.00,1200.00,NULL,'2015-02-01 08:00:00','2015-01-20 08:00:00',NULL,'2015-01-28 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,'','','','As it is stated above registration of associations is vital and foundation without license they will not be permitted to work, deal in the market and ask for the law- full rights of them from government departments. They will be organized and will recognized as strong sources of business and having a good licit income, in light of that Mercy Corps- SAGAL decided to pay a part of association costs. In realty the registration process needs more time and expanses due to government policies and the stakeholders are higher rather than the program. SAGAL will pay legal cost of registration based on providing of documents, and facilitate the registration process of association formation, this activity will consist of the following task/steps:\r\n\r\nFacilitating Meeting with People for forming the Association\r\nThe activity should be coordinated with line departments. \r\nVoting for selection of key members and Preparing of necessary documents by assisting program staff.\r\nPresenting of request letter to PGO for getting approvals/ assignment to DoJ for further process.\r\nFulfilment of all DoJ’s required documents including (Crime Record checking), based on DoJ policy.\r\nThe key members will be introduced to MoJ by DoJ with all provided documents, for finalizing the process.\r\nReceiving of the license from MoJ and submitting a copy of license to DoJ\r\nSpreading and propagating of the license copy to all governmental departments by DoJ.\r\n','','','2015-12-06 09:16:13','2015-12-06 09:16:13',NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,8,67,3,39,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(15,NULL,'Exhibition of Ag-Inputs for the Market Linkage - Input Suppliers','32550A052','','1.2.1 Support Input Suppliers and Private Sector','','8500','713','',0,'','1.	The farmers will be linked to Ag-Inputs suppliers, for easy, timely, inexpensively and regularly access to Ag-Inputs; in addition the agriculture sector and farm services will be developed and improved indirectly.\r\n2.	The Ag-Inputs Suppliers would be linked to each other; the Ag-Inputs supplement services and business would be expanded and developed. \r\n','0015-01-21 08:00:00','0015-01-31 08:00:00','','','','','',1107.00,1107.00,NULL,'2015-01-15 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Description of Project and Activities:\r\nThis project will be consist of the following steps and tasks:\r\n\r\n1.	The first meeting with BISA for coordination and arrangement of the Ag-Inputs Exhibition \r\n2.	Preparing of all the required documents(Financial and Administrative Documents) \r\n3.	Arrangement and coordination of the participants list with BISA.\r\n4.	Conducting of (Exhibition of Ag-Inputs for the Market Linkage).\r\n5.	Collection of the required documents using in the activity report such as pictures, payments sheets and etc.\r\n6.	Final completion report.\r\n','','','2015-12-08 06:10:55','2015-12-08 06:10:55',NULL,NULL,NULL,6,NULL,NULL,7,67,3,6,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55','2015-01-15',60885.00,60885.00,'',NULL),(233,NULL,'WUA-Maturity Assessment','91115A001','','2.1 Conduct Maturity Assessment of the existing 10 WUA','','8500/8530','91115L012','',0,'','Based on the  results of this assessment, further needs of the water users associations will be determined, further gaps will be assessed and capacity building activities for developing and strengthening of the institutional and organization capacity of water users associations will be developed.  \r\n','2015-08-13 07:00:00','2015-08-30 07:00:00','','','','','',200.00,200.00,4,'2015-08-10 07:00:00','2015-08-10 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Since 2007, Mercy Corps (MC) through EC founded Kunduz integrated Water Initiative KIWI-1 and KIWI-2 programs has helped farmers to establish and strengthen 10 Water Users’ Associations (WUA) and 36 Water Users’ Groups (WUG).\r\n MC helped farmers to establish WUA, supported them to rehabilitate and construct small-scale irrigation infrastructures, improved their governance through training in water management, legal issues and good governance, and adopting new, more water efficient, agriculture and irrigation practices and supported them to become the first WUAs in Afghanistan to be registered. In order to sustain this achievement in the development of social water management through WUA under the Water Law( 2009), there are challenges that require multi-year funding streams to overcome.\r\n \r\nThe challenges to developing the sustainable and inclusive management across the river basin level require interventions to strengthen the administrative efficacy of the Panj-Amu River Basin Agency as well as strengthening the institutional capacity of the WUAs.\r\n \r\n In order to assess the administrative and institutional capacity building requirement of the WUAs, it is proposed that a maturity assessment of the 10 existing WUAs established be conducted, in Kunduz, Chardara, Qalai Zal and Alia bad districts of Kunduz province and Baghlan Jadid, Pole Khumri and Nuhreen districts of Baghlan province. Based on the  results of this assessment, the needs of the associations will be identified, capacity building activities will be prioritized and trainings will be conducted.\r\n','','','2015-11-30 10:12:27','2015-11-30 10:12:27',NULL,NULL,NULL,26,NULL,NULL,10,168,3,NULL,10,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55 AFN','2015-08-10',11000.00,11000.00,'',NULL),(222,NULL,'Market Forum Meeting – Watermelon Market System','32550A062','','2.1.1: Value Chain Analysis','','8500','721','',0,'','The stakeholders in the market system/ value chain will be able to identify gaps in the entire value chains and look for appropriate solutions either through engaging with themselves in small groups or seeking support from relevant other stakeholders.\r\nThe stakeholders engaged in the chain will start to find meaning in taking the issues confronting the value chain/market system and form a forum to engage in the longer-term to discuss progress and challenges. ','2015-04-15 07:00:00','2015-04-30 07:00:00','','','','','',345.00,345.00,NULL,'2015-04-12 07:00:00','2015-11-10 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'approved','2015-12-08 08:00:00','','','','Hilmand SAGAL conducted the PMDS workshop within Dec-2014, so based on the participants list provided through aforementioned workshop all of them will be invited to participate in the market forum meeting, any required facilities such as stationery, transportation cost, incentives, meeting venue with all requirements would be provided as well, the market forum meeting  would be facilitated by Hilmand SAGAl team directly, the previous information such as noted gapes, issues, problems, challenges and action points would be shared with all participants during this meeting, finally all of the presented new information and action points would be noted and listed as well  for coming plan.','','','2015-12-08 10:38:13','2015-12-08 10:38:13',98,98,NULL,34,NULL,NULL,7,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55','2015-04-12',18975.00,18975.00,'',NULL),(223,NULL,'IPM training to farmers through DAIL','32550A063','','1.1.2 Build DAIL extension services capacity','','8500','712','',0,'','The participants would be able to control plant diseases and pests and increase the production of licit crops, form other side the contents of the IPM training is a combination of 5 different methods of pest control such as mechanical, cultural,  Biological, physical and finally chemical, so the environment would be saved cleanly and will not be polluted by chemicals.','2015-04-21 07:00:00','2015-04-30 07:00:00','','','','','',1046.00,1046.00,NULL,'2015-04-21 07:00:00','2015-11-10 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'approved','2015-12-08 08:00:00','','','','This is a one day training program financially supported by MCA/SAGAL,  the total 80 participants would be divided into two groups, each group will be consist of 40 trainees, every single group will be trained within separate day but the training topic will be the same (IPM) for the entire participants. before training started all of the requirements should be arranged and managed as follwoing:\r\nFirstly a meeting will be held with DAIL director and Plant Protection Department manager for discussing on training requirements and relevant responsibilities. \r\nSecondly all the require documents will be prepared like PA, BOQ, participants list, attendance sheets, payment sheets, PRs, Order Forms, training schedule, exchanging formal letters with DAIL, and other relevant departments and etc. \r\nThirdly the training materials will be coordinated with introduced trainer/extension worker;  the project will be implemented within two days and finally photos will be taken during  the implementation of this project for the preparation of completion and activity reports.        ','','','2015-12-08 10:28:10','2015-12-08 10:28:10',98,98,NULL,34,NULL,NULL,7,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55','2015-04-21',57530.00,57530.00,'',NULL),(16,NULL,'Marketing training - agriculture input suppliers, traders - processors','32550A006','','Marketing training - agriculture input suppliers, traders - processors','','8500','713','',0,'','The business of Input Suppliers will be promoted and improved and they will be able to maintain good business relationship to the relevant market chain actors, this will result in strengthening the market linkages as well as increase in sales and profitability.','2015-02-08 08:00:00','2015-02-25 08:00:00','','','','','',204.00,204.00,3,'2015-02-01 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,'','','','Traders, processors and agriculture input-suppliers involved in SAGAL selected valu