h line departments in Kandahar to improve DAIL organizational capacity aiming to deliver better and more effective extension services. \r\n\r\nSince Herat province has become one of the largest producer of saffron in Afghanistan as well as having experience of more than 10 years’ of saffron cultivation. Mercy Corps HV PHDP team, hence planned this exposure visit for government staff in Herat. The government employees are expected to obtain the knowledge and experience about saffron cultivation, collection, packing/packaging and marketing. This learning exposure visit is further expected to contribute in improving DAIL staff saffron cultivation skills.\r\n','2015-10-25 07:00:00','2015-11-30 08:00:00','','','','','',4150.00,4150.00,NULL,'2015-10-21 07:00:00','2015-10-21 07:00:00',NULL,'2015-10-21 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,'Approved ','','','As mentioned five governmental staff (3 DAIL staff, 1 Sectorial (G.O) staff and 1 DCN staff) will participate in exposure visit to Herat province.','','','2015-12-08 08:50:02','2015-12-08 08:50:02',103,103,NULL,104,NULL,NULL,5,167,38,103,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55','2015-10-10',228250.00,228250.00,'',NULL),(18,NULL,'TOT-Good Governance Training to DDAs & CSos','32550A008','',' DDAs Linked to CSOs','','8500','742','',0,'','1.	Building sub-national governance linkages between DDAs and CSOs will enhance their capacity to coordinate well on community issues with relevant governmental institutions and so far contribute in community development on district and provincial level. \r\n2.	There will be better communication linkages between DDAs and CSOs members as well as they could smoothly coordinate and cooperate with government departments in the future.\r\n3.	The DDAs members will train the CDCs members in the districts and CDCs will deliver the same trainings to the people who are living in their districts.\r\n','2015-02-20 08:00:00','2015-03-10 07:00:00','','','',''