livering training will conduct the pre and post training evaluation tests. All activities related to finance, procurement and logistics will be properly planned, documented and approved, and the BOQ for this training is annexed to this PA.  This training will cover describing Role of law, constitution of Afghanistan, kinds and steps of law, effective of law on society and promotion, regulation of law and other relevant and necessary topics. \r\n','','','2015-11-30 03:08:28','2015-11-30 03:08:28',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,8,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,1140.00,0.00,'',NULL),(33,NULL,'Conflict resolution training to DDAs, CDCs and CSOs ',' 32550A013','','Conflict resolution training to DDAs, CDCs and CSOs ','','8500','741','',0,'','The DDAs, CDCs and CSOs members of Tarin Kot and Dihrawud District will fully understand about the Conflict resolution system.\r\nAfter training trainees will be able that how they can solve their problems and conflicts, how they can reduce risk and problems, how they can prepare safety society, what are the responsibilities of government and society about conflict resolution, how they can to create peaceful environment and how they can remove distance between society and government. \r\n','2015-04-08 07:00:00','2015-04-30 07:00:00','','','','','',860.00,860.00,3,'2015-04-08 07:00:00','2015-04-15 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,'','','','Urozgan SAGAL team will conduct 3 days conflict resolution training to 20 representatives of DDAs, CSOs and CDS SCOs coordination with DDAs will introduce worthy trainees and manage training room. \r\nSAGAL team will select a qualified trainer who will prepare the training modules according to the need assessment and besides delivering training will conduct the pre and post training evaluation tests. All activities related to finance, procurement and logistics will be properly planned, documented and approved, and the BOQ for this training is annexed to this PA.  This training will cover describing of conflict, kinds and causes of conflicts and effective roles of conflict resolution.  \r\n','','','2015-11-30 03:10:54','2015-11-30 03:10:54',NULL,NULL,NULL,8,NULL,NULL,8,67,3,8,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(279,NULL,'Saffron Cultivation – Saffron Corms Distribution & Planting','32717A001','','2.1.1 Introduce farmers to new techniques to undertake the pilot and demonstration crop cultivation of selected crops through provision of inputs and services)','','8210','32717L004','',0,'','Saffron is a high – value medicinal plant that was introduced to Herat Province a decade ago under the “Research in Alternative Livelihoods Fund (RALF)”. It has shown adaptability in and around Kandahar City and Districts to the north and west of the city. Saffron was first tested at Kandahar University’s Research and Extension Farm in 2007. Saffron corms are not typically expected to send up many flowers in the first year, but under the Kandahar soil and Climatic conditions, saffron tested at Kandahar University did produce a nominal yield in the first year itself. The project will support the earlier initiative and expand the cultivation of saffron cultivation through supporting existing farmer associations.\r\n\r\nIn order to promote saffron component in Kandahar, Mercy Corps HVPHDP Program will work with 100 farmers in 0.5 jerib/farmer through associations in Dand, Daman, Panjwai and Khakrez districts on Saffron cultivation, processing and marketing in order to promote and extend saffron cultivation in Kandahar enabling farmer communities to create licit alternative. The farmers will be selected by Associations and will be verified by DDA, and local agriculture extensions departments in district level.\r\n\r\nUnder the program umbrella selected farmers will propagate saffron by cultivating, processing and marketing in with close collaboration of Saffron Associations in all districts. The farmers will also provide their demonstration plots to other farmers for field days and conducting practical sessions.\r\n  \r\nWith the course of the program selected farmers in all four districts will receive 50kg Saffron Corms/each total 100x50=5000kg. The program target groups will include Lead Farmers, Farmers, DAIL Extension Department, Public Agricultural Research Agencies ,Input Suppliers, Nursery Growers, Farmer Based Association, Financial Institutions, Sub-Governance farm structures &civil society Human Rights and Gender \r\n','2015-09-10 07:00:00','2015-12-10 08:00:00','','','','','',19500.00,19500.00,NULL,'2015-09-09 07:00:00','2015-09-09 07:00:00',NULL,'2015-09-09 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,'','','','After the obtaining the 100 lead farmer list from the four mentioned associations the PHPD program team will carry on the following tasks:\r\n●	Meetings and Consultation with DAIL, DDC and Saffron Associations \r\n●	Identify Targeted districts in Kandahar \r\n●	Verify the lead farmers through extension agents and DDA\r\n●	Identify technical suitability for Saffron cultivation at farmer level\r\n●	Raising purchasing request (PR) for the procurement of the 5000kg saffron corm\r\n●	Distribution of the saffron corm to the lead farmers\r\n●	Planting of Saffron Corm\r\n','','','2015-12-02 03:33:32','2015-12-02 03:33:32',NULL,NULL,NULL,104,NULL,NULL,5,167,39,103,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55','2015-09-08',1072500.00,1072500.00,'',NULL),(217,NULL,'DAIL staff Exposure Visit to Nangrahar Province','32550A059','','1.1.2 Build DAIL extension services capacity','','8500','712','',0,'','The major outcomes or impacts of this project will be as below:\r\nThe capacity of Hilmand-DAIL/extension department officials will be enhanced by visiting the Agribusiness projects done in Nangrahar Province\r\nThe supported DAIL/extension agents will be able to expand the acquired knowledge and experiences with their co-workers and farmers\r\nThe linkages between SAGAL and DAIL will come up stronger and efficient.','2015-03-22 07:00:00','2015-04-14 07:00:00','','','','','',2604.00,2604.00,NULL,'2015-03-16 07:00:00','2015-11-09 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,'','','','This exposure visit will be considered as TOT and participants will be expected to propagate the learned knowledge to rest of DAIL officials and will similarly train farmers under facilitation by SAGAL program. \r\n\r\nThis project will consist of the following tasks:\r\nCoordination meetings and deal with Hilmand DAIL (Department of Agriculture, Irrigation and Livestock).\r\nExchanging of information and formal letters for introducing the participants\r\nPreparing of all the required Financial, Logistic & Administrative Documents.\r\nConducting of 6 days exposure visit as following:\r\n●   Day1: trip from HLD-KBL-JAA\r\n●  Day2: visit to Horticultural Orchards\r\n●  Day3: visit to Vegetable Fields/ green houses\r\n●  Day4: visit to Processing/ Packing companies\r\n●  Day5: visit of private sector until 12:00PM and trip from JAA-KBL after 01:00PM\r\n●   Day6: trip from KBL-HLD\r\nCollection of the required documents using in the activity report and writing of activity completion report.','','','2015-12-08 09:06:02','2015-12-08 09:06:02',NULL,NULL,NULL,34,NULL,NULL,7,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55','2015-03-16',143220.00,143220.00,'',NULL),(218,NULL,'Financial awareness workshop - stakeholders','32550A060','','3.1.1 Farmer Financial Awareness Building','','8500','731','',0,'','Through this workshop various stakeholders will get information on Islamic banking presents by financial institutions, and will be able to find easy and smoothly access to loan products/packages.\r\nIn case of stakeholders’ willingness and access to loan packages the agriculture products will be increa