ject will increase .63 000 kg in red meat and the cost will be $360.000,generate faster income to the farmers and present healthier meat to the consumers ,encourage farmers to use concentrate feed and use quality vaccine and medication .It also will concrete linkages between farmers ,VFUs and market.','2014-04-01 07:00:00','2014-06-30 07:00:00','','','','','',5464.00,5464.00,5,'2014-04-01 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Vaccination/medication: The selected animals will be vaccinated/ de-wormed by Para-Vets the type pf vaccines needed has to be applied, or confirmed that is applied to selected lambs. MC-HASP purchase vaccines and medication from viable source due to quality and certification and Para-Vets will apply based on the MOU to the targeted 3,000 selected lambs. Total cost of vaccination/de-worming ear tag will be 100 AFA per animal excluding operation cost. Pasteurellosis, sheep and goat pox, enterotoxaemia, peste des petites ruminants (PPR), FMD Foot and mouth anthrax diseases and albandazole for de-worming.	\r\nEar tagging: During lamb fattening project ear tagging is very important, indicating of animals, measuring of project impact, measuring of gained weight, and comparing animals with those lambs were not feed. Ear tagging will be managed by Para-Vets (High).\r\nBody weighting of lambs: Body weight of animal will be done by Para-Vets every two weeks and the gained weight will record in special sheet developed by HASP and reported to office.\r\nOnce the list of beneficiaries is provided and verified by PVD Para-Vets will start vaccination/de-worming, ear tagging before the feed is started to the animals. \r\n','','','2015-11-23 06:47:09','2015-11-23 06:47:09',NULL,NULL,NULL,4,NULL,NULL,7,63,25,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Nil',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(69,NULL,'Livestock  Value Chain Support','LKGA033-14','','Distribution of animal feed firs phase ','','8540','072','',0,'','