e cross visit Meet with the selected meat processing plants, meat dealers and butcher shops the main focus for the cross (e.g. visit the meat plants, review the meat market and exchange the ideas with local butcher shops). Ask meat plant owner what they buy and how many animals they need on monthly or daily bases. They have to share their experiences with the farmers they visit.\r\n2.  Select which farmers need to attend the cross visit \r\nFind out who does the work with the livestock– these are the people who need to attend the cross visit. What is their language? Do they have written language? Aim for no more than 5 meat dealers.\r\n3. Staff meeting to Plan\r\nListing the resources the visitors will need on the day of the cross visit, and work out who will supply them. For example, the need to take notebook and pens/markers, a camera, and keep visiting farmers to a maximum of 6 to 10 people. \r\nIf they don’t read or write, use diagrams and photos. Discuss and agree on the best approach to make sure target audience can attend the cross visit;\r\n4. Plan the visitor group feedback session\r\nPlan each step in the process: Plan each step in the process: Prepare sheets of paper for visitors to write down what they have learnt what they will take back to their communities and how cross visits could be improved.\r\n5. Encourage farmers to ask questions and talk about their own experiences.\r\nEncourage them to identify what they will need to know in order to do similar practices at the village (e.g. do their cultivation methods are the same as they saw during visit? Do you have the same problems at the village? Will this practice work at your place?)\r\n\r\nCross visits of farmers to other provinces to learn and exchange their experiences with other skilled farmers. \r\n','','','2015-11-23 07:26:34','2015-11-23 07:26:34',NULL,NULL,NULL,4,NULL,NULL,7,63,16,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Nil',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NU