15-06-04 07:00:00','','','','','',991.64,991.64,NULL,'2015-05-07 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Mercy Corps will train existed associations heads or board members in proposal writing so that they can” and are able to write the proposal for their associations and running their associations smoothly. There will be 10 associations (Irrigation, Nursery Growers and Greenhouse growers Associations) from Nangarhar, Kunar and Laghman provinces and 2 members from each association, the total participants will be 20 and the training will be in the following topics.\r\n\r\n●	The proposal writing style\r\n●	The proposal writing importance \r\n●	Components of a Proposal\r\n1.	Executive summary \r\n2.	Statement of need (why this project is necessary?)\r\n3.	Project description (nuts and bolts of how the project will be implemented and evaluated?)\r\n4.	Budget (Financial description of the project plus explanatory notes)\r\n5.	Organization information (history and governing structure of the nonprofit, its primary activities audiences and services)\r\n6.	Conclusion (summary of the proposal’s main points)\r\n●	Main point of the needs \r\n●	Problems explanation\r\n●	Common goal\r\n●	Project objectives \r\n●	Strategy for purpose achievement\r\n●	The project expectations\r\n●	Implementing strategy and project management.\r\n●	Monitoring and evaluation\r\n●	External factors ( risks and restriction)\r\n●	Project resource and budget and so on. \r\n\r\nThe following activities will be undertaken during implementation of the project:\r\n1.	Selection of training participants.\r\n2.	Coordinate the training idea with the trainer and get their confirmation.\r\n3.	Preparation of training plan and training conducting schedule.\r\n4.	Procurement process.\r\n5.	Start conducting of the training according to the schedule.\r\n6.	Disseminating and providing of training material.\r\n7.	Regular technical assistance and monitoring conducting.\r\n8.	Evaluation of the training.\r\n9.	Prepare training recommendation and completion report\r\n','','','2015-12-10 10:38:03','2015-12-10 10:38:03',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,10,4,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','1$=AFN 55','2015-05-07',54540.20,54540.20,'',NULL),(78,NULL,'CoMo staff  Training - 90939A009','90939A009','','Staff Capacity building training','','5610','210   90939  ','',0,'','This training will enable the DDA members to become more active and well administrate DDA members for their district\r\nOne of the main objective of SPNA is to build the capacity of DDA members, therefore, it is designed to conduct these training projects to skill up DDA members in the three mentioned districts. \r\n','2013-02-12 08:00:00','2013-02-25 08:00:00','','','','','',174.02,174.02,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','DDA requested that it is one of their need to develop their capacity to carry with their activities in proper manner in 3 target districts.\r\n\r\nThis training will cover 3 below topics:\r\n1.	Gender Planning \r\n2.	Conflict resolution\r\n3.	Natural Resource Management\r\n 1-To develop the capacity of DDA, 2- Raise their knowledge of management, 3-Develop their conflict management, NRM and gender planning skills, 4- Improve their attitude and to enable them to become an active partner for the government , NGOs and NSP councils in the districts','','','2015-12-13 15:37:11','2015-12-13 15:37:11',NULL,NULL,NULL,36,NULL,NULL,6,66,3,NULL,10,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(432,NULL,'DDA Capacity Building Training - 90939A010','90939A010','','Capacity Building workshop','','8500/8530','310   90939  ','',0,'','One of the main objective of SPNA is to build the capacity of DDA members, therefore, it is designed to conduct these training projects to skill up DDA members in the three mentioned districts. \r\nThis training will enable the DDA members to become mo