ational and international institutions. Also the DDA will find the skill of proving its accountability and community acceptation. \r\n','2013-10-06 07:00:00','2013-10-24 07:00:00','','','','','',4982.73,4982.73,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','DDA requested that it is one of their needs to develop their capacity to carry with their activities in proper manner in 3 target districts.\r\n(g and Evaluation on district level. \r\nAt the start of the Training activity\r\n	Introduce yourself and explain your role as facilitator/ trainer\r\n	If the group does not know each other well, give people a few minutes to introduce themselves before\r\nyou start the activity\r\n	Ensure that everyone in the group understands the purpose of the training/ activity and how they will\r\nwork together as a group\r\n	Agree on the way everyone will work together. For example:\r\n	All contributions are valued\r\n	We all share responsibility for facilitation\r\n	One person speaks at a time\r\n	Identify any missing people or groups\r\n	Start with a story: it is good to begin a training by telling a brief story that is relevant to the focus of\r\nthe activity\r\nDuring the training\r\n	Manage the training so that everyone can participate and contribute\r\n	Use appropriate language and give respect to all people\r\n	Make no judgements about what people say and encourage people to see each other’s point of view\r\n	Use ‘powerful listening’: listening very attentively to people helps them to speak more clearly and\r\npowerfully, especially quieter or less confident people\r\n	Write a summary of any information or decisions on large sheets of paper or blackboard so that\r\neveryone can see\r\n	Collect all of the information from the group, then make decisions about it\r\n	Give careful attention to the aim of the training and intervene if people do not keep to these aims or if\r\nparts of the activity take too long\r\nAt the end of the training\r\n	Encourage appreciation for everyone’s participation and ideas\r\n	Ensure that everyone knows if they must do anything after the training\r\n','','','2015-12-13 07:58:00','2015-12-13 07:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,36,NULL,NULL,6,66,3,NULL,10,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(427,NULL,'VSALs somali','','','','','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,'','','','','',0.00,0.00,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','2015-11-30 13:01:14','2015-11-30 13:01:14',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,186,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(428,NULL,'VSLA Formation in somali region','','','','','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,'','','','','',0.00,0.00,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','2015-11-30 13:08:41','2015-11-30 13:08:41',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,186,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(433,NULL,'test','','','','','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,'','','','','',0.00,0.00,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','2015-11-30 20:47:42','2015-11-30 20:47:42',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,153,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(434,NULL,'SRS - Range land management  (updated)','10/03','','Improved pasture situation ','','91104','L107','',0,'','	Well sensitized community on the area of range land management (protection, care, and wisely usage)\r\n	Well organized range land management committee \r\n	Animal science expertise from the livestock offices are given ToT  training on range land protection and management \r\n	Target community members are training on range land protection, better management and empowered their decisions towards the environment.\r\n	Improved healthier grazing land through better range