 land, water and vegetation management and use based on an integrated approach to land resources development with the direct involvement and participation of the different actors. Implementing watershed resource management practices with the involvement of the local communities to improve the economic and environmental values/services of the resources and thereby to contribute towards food security, livelihoods of the community and to maintain the benefits of the environment for the coming generation.  BRACED program aimed to implement Participatory Natural Resource Management approach to support climate-resilient green development planning, and help secure rights to natural resource use and management. This concept note is, therefore; developed to conduct the selection of rehabilitation sites for watershed development in all intervention woreda.','2015-11-30 08:00:00','2015-12-31 08:00:00','','','','','',1637.00,1637.00,NULL,'2015-11-30 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-12-01 08:00:00','2015-12-01 08:00:00','in progress','2015-12-02 08:00:00','','','','Discussions and planning with Segen and Gamo Gofa zones and the four woreda agriculture offices. Criteria development for the selection of rehabilitation sites in each woreda. Joint assessment of rehabilitation sites/degraded watersheds/ in all woreda. Selection of two rehabilitation sites in each woreda based on the criteria developed \r\n','','','2015-12-11 06:10:22','2015-12-11 06:10:22',NULL,126,NULL,123,141,NULL,38,200,34,123,10,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','21','2015-11-30',34364.00,34364.00,'',NULL),(418,NULL,'VSALs somali region','','','','','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,'','','','','',0.00,0.00,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','','','','2015-11-30 11:50:47','2015-11-30 11:50:47',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,186,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(419,NULL,'SNNPRS-Range land Management Site selection ','2.3.1.1','','Range land management sites will be selected in consultation with Woreda Agriculture Office and beneficiary communities in Konso  Woreda ','','8530','91104L107','',0,'','•	Two range land management sites selected and mapped in Konso woreda \r\n•	community and woreda officials consulted on the Way forward discussed\r\n ','2015-11-30 08:00:00','2015-12-31 08:00:00','','','','','',1612.00,1612.00,NULL,'2015-11-27 08:00:00','2015-12-01 08:00:00',NULL,'2015-12-01 08:00:00','2015-12-04 08:00:00','2015-12-04 08:00:00','in progress','2015-12-14 08:00:00','It will be approved after having discussion with the BRACED SNNPRS team','','','BRACED is a three years project implemented by a consortium of four organizations such as Farm Africa, Mercy Corps, Lions Heads and LTSI. The main objective of the project is to test innovative market based approaches to improve the resilience of economic, ecological and social systems to open opportunities for vulnerable pastoral/agro-pastoral households, businesses and communities in rural and peri-urban areas to better manage risk and resources, and successfully transform their livelihoods should they choose to. Mercy Corps SNNPR cluster program is expected to directly benefit 91,785 vulnerable people particularly women and children in Segen and Gamo Gofa zones. Land use change from rangelands to crop agriculture decreases the resilience of the lowland communities and ecosystems for climate extremes. Deforestation and rangeland degradation decreases the quality of soils, increases erosion and run-off and thereby reduce rangeland productivity. BRACED program planned to implement Participatory Rangeland Resource Management approach to support climate-resilient green development planning, and help secure rights to natural resource use and management. Therefore; the objective of this concept note is to enable the BRACED team to conduct Rangeland area assessment, resource identificati