 literacy training.\r\n8.	SAGAL Community mobilization team will arrange training on district level.  \r\n9.	Put PR and make a reasonable budget sheet for the expenditure of the Financial Literacy Trainings. \r\n10.	Provide report on the workshop and make a conclusion of Financial Literacy Trainings.\r\n','','','2015-12-06 09:58:21','2015-12-06 09:58:21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','1$=AFN 55','2015-03-17',19660.10,126160.10,'',NULL),(210,NULL,'SRS- Training and familirization for Newly recruited BRACED staff held at Jijiga somali regional state ','10/01','','SRS- Staff familiarization and launching workshop (updated)','','1000000151511','','',0,'','It is to be recalled that, as one of the key steps of   implementation of BRACED   start-up  activities, internal workshop was organized and  conducted from August 26-28, 2015 in Addis Ababa  which helped  to bring about  a shared understanding among  the consortium members  about the vision, objectives , strategies , financial management and reporting procedures of BRACED program. Currently signing of project agreements with the Somali Regional Government, recruitment of key field level staff and preparation for opening of field offices is finalized and hence it is found vital to conduct field level staff familiarization training and launching of regional workshop. ','2015-10-05 07:00:00','2015-10-07 07:00:00','','','','','',133.00,133.00,NULL,'2015-05-11 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-10-04 07:00:00',NULL,'approved',NULL,'this concept note is already approved manually','','','The consequences of climate change, rapid urbanization, deforestation and related factors are impacting climate resilience in Ethiopia’s lowlands including the Somali Region.: Financial services are currently weak in lowland areas, and the resulting low levels of savings and credit reduce household climate resilience. Together these issues limit the resilience of ecological, social and economic systems to cope with or respond to climate-related shocks\r\n\r\nA DFID funded BRACED Program, which will be implemented by  four consortium members (Farm Africa (Lead organisation), Mercy Corps, Lion’s Head International and LTSI), is designed  to directly benefit 84,285 vulnerable people in three zones of (Korahe, Degehabur and Gode) of Somali Region   particularly women and children by helping them become more resilient to climate extremes. The project’s overarching goal is to pilot market-based mechanisms to help improve pastoralist resilience will generate robust impact evidence, which in turn will draw in greater private sector engagement and investment into the lowlands\r\n','','','2015-12-11 14:02:35','2015-12-11 14:02:35',NULL,NULL,NULL,115,120,54,35,200,34,114,19,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','20','2015-05-11',2660.00,2660.00,'',NULL),(230,NULL,'Grapes’ post harvesting handling training to extension agents- TOT','32550A068','','1.1.2 Build DAIL extension services capacity','','8500','712','',0,'','Fresh graduates of the Hilmand Agriculture Faculty as beneficiaries of this training and extension agents will fully understand about SAGAL program’s objectives and activities, they will be able to train farmers on district levels and MCA- SAGAL will facilitate those trainings in SAGAL targeted districts. These Agriculture graduates are expected to expand similar trainings to farmers in selected value chains; as a result the technical capacity of farmers will be enhanced.','2015-06-14 07:00:00','2015-06-30 07:00:00','','','','','',340.00,340.00,NULL,'2015-06-11 07:00:00','2015-11-11 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','SAGAL Hilmand team will facilitate to organize one day post-harvest management training under technical consultation and guidance of Agriculture Faculty of the Hilmand University, the University/Agriculture Faculty will introduce 21 fresh gradua