L,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','55','2015-06-23',19580.00,19580.00,'',NULL),(234,NULL,'Operation and Maintenance Training for 10 Water User Association','91115A002','','1.1: Train WUA to develop and manage their O&M plans and internal budget ','','8500/8530','91115L012','',0,'','As a result of operation and maintenance training the technical knowledge of the water users associations’ board members Will be increased \r\nthey will be able to know the extreme importance and necessity of operation and maintenance practices to be considered  and administered throughout the command area for ensuring proper operation and maintenance of the irrigation structures and infrastructures, as well as conducting of this training will impact on sustainable operating and maintenance of the irrigation structures\r\n\r\n','2015-11-04 08:00:00','2016-03-30 07:00:00','','','','','',1406.27,1256.27,4,'2015-10-27 07:00:00','2015-11-15 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Since 2007, Mercy Corps (MC) through EC founded Kunduz integrated Water Initiative KIWI-1 and KIWI-2 programs has helped farmers to establish and strengthen 10 Water Users’ Associations (WUA) and 36 Water Users’ Groups (WUG).\r\nMC helped farmers to establish WUA, supported them to rehabilitate and construct small-scale irrigation infrastructures, improved their governance through training in water management, legal issues and good governance, and adopting new, more water efficient, agriculture and irrigation practices and supported them to become the first WUAs in Afghanistan to be registered. In order to sustain this achievement in the development of social water management through WUA under the Water Law( 2009), there are challenges that require multi-year funding streams to overcome.\r\n\r\nThe challenges to developing the sustainable and inclusive management across the river basin level require interventions to strengthen the administrative efficacy of the Panj-Amu River Basin Agency as well as strengthening the institutional capacity of the WUAs.\r\n\r\nThe irrigation structures and infrastructures under command area of WUA are not being operating and maintaining properly, while, they operate and manage traditionally without having any proper plans for operation and maintenance activities due to lack of knowledge and low capacity of operation and maintenance practices,  which causes poor water delivery services, being disordered condition of irrigation system,not guarantee the sustainability and equal  allocation of water resource. \r\n \r\n In order to address the above said challenges and  increase the technical  knowledge and build the capacity of the  WUAs, it is proposed that operation and maintenance training should be conducted for  10 existing WUAs, in Kunduz, Chardara, Qalai Zal and Alia bad districts of Kunduz province and Baghlan Jadid, Pole Khumri and Nuhreen districts of Baghlan province. \r\nIt is worth mentioning that after delivering this training two follow up meeting will be conducted individually with each of the WUA ( Head, Secretory & Mirab) one follow up meeting will be held in November,2015 and the second will be held in March,2016,to bring in practice the delivered topic a full day practical work will be carried out with them to ensure their complete understanding and ability to develop operation and maintenance plan for the coming irrigation season. To make sure that  there is a visit form developed by program team based on the requirement of donor to be filled in  during the follow up meeting and approved by the representative of WUA as evidence ( Minutes)and will be submitted with Bi-Monthly report to  donor \r\n','','','2015-11-30 10:23:23','2015-11-30 10:23:23',NULL,NULL,NULL,26,NULL,NULL,10,168,3,NULL,10,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','60 AFN','2015-10-27',75376.20,84376.20,'',NULL),(262,NULL,'Exposure visit - Market for Association','32550A021','','2.2.4 Exposure to markets for Associations','','8500','726','',0,'','The Nursery growers will enhance the production and planting process of timber trees at their nurseries and also expecting to maintain a business entity to promote timbers’ cutting in the region. \r\nFarmers will have access to get varietal wise timbers at their region. ','2014-12-02 08:00:00','2014-12-10 08:00:00','','','','','',4384.00,2384.00,NULL,NULL,'2014-12-02 08:00:00',NULL,'2014-12-02 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,'approved',NULL,'','','','Mercy Corps – SAGAL will Select the nursery growers that need to go on the exposure visit and Meet with those eastern region members who are really interested and have good background in this field, visit the Timber cultivation in Kabul Guldara District and bring them back with some idea and experience to share it with other Associations members.\r\nListing the resources the visitors will need on the day of the cross visit, and work out who will supply them. For example, the need to take notebook and pens/markers, a camera, and keep visiting relevant people to this visit to a maximum of 6 to 10 people. \r\nIf they don’t read or write, use diagrams and photos. Discuss and agree on the best approach to make sure target audience can attend the exposure visit; \r\nPrepare sheets of paper for visitors to write down what they have learnt what they will take back to their communities and how exposure visits could be improved.\r\nEncourage them to develop a plan to undertake the nursery of the timber cuttings. Develop a timeline, resources required, and the size of the nursery that needs to be planted.','','','2015-12-06 09:06:37','2015-12-06 09:06:37',NULL,NULL,NULL,100,NULL,NULL,5,67,3,102,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,0.00,'',NULL),(236,NULL,'Second Market Forum Meeting – Watermelon Market System','32550A071','','2.1.1: Value Chain Analysis','','8500','721','',0,'','The stakeholders in the market system/ value chain w