 will be able to know the extreme importance and necessity of irrigation service fee to be promoted and administered within the command area of WUA and a sustainable and reliable  income source will be established, besides, in the consequence of budget development training the knowledge and information level of the water users association will be enhanced and they will also be encouraged to prepare financial plan for the implementation of  their operation and maintenance plan ','2015-12-05 08:00:00','2016-01-31 08:00:00','','','','','',1406.27,1256.27,4,'2015-11-28 08:00:00','2015-10-28 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Since 2007, Mercy Corps (MC) through EC founded Kunduz integrated Water Initiative KIWI-1 and KIWI-2 programs has helped farmers to establish and strengthen 10 Water Users’ Associations (WUA) and 36 Water Users’ Groups (WUG).\r\nMC helped farmers to establish WUA, supported them to rehabilitate and construct small-scale irrigation infrastructures, improved their governance through training in water management, legal issues and good governance, and adopting new, more water efficient, agriculture and irrigation practices and supported them to become the first WUAs in Afghanistan to be registered. In order to sustain this achievement in the development of social water management through WUA under the Water Law( 2009), there are challenges that require multi-year funding streams to overcome.\r\n\r\nThe challenges to developing the sustainable and inclusive management across the river basin level require interventions to strengthen the administrative efficacy of the Panj-Amu River Basin Agency as well as strengthening the institutional capacity of the WUAs.\r\n\r\nIn general, all WUA  currently do not have any income source to finance and support water management systems and achieve their goals, mostly they rely on external financial support received from government and NGOs which is not provided on suitable time and season so that commonly they are centralized and dependent on external financial resources which not allow them to be independent and freely make decision for the maintenance of the irrigation systems ,  in fact irrigation service fee is one of the most momentous activity for the implementation of  social water management particularly for the implementation of operation and maintenance plans\r\n\r\nWater User Associations ( WUA) usually do not prepare or develop any financial plan for operation and maintenance of irrigation canals and other           structures so that they neither anticipate the source of income nor they know about the expected amount of  expenditure, even though they are not able to decide well and predict the coming year income and expenses due to no exist of budget plan, at the meanwhile, although there is no budgetary program it has also caused that the irrigation service fee system does not exist.\r\n \r\nIn order to address the above said challenges and  increase the technical  knowledge, build the capacity of the  WUAs, it is proposed to facilitate ISF and budget preparation trainings which enable the WUAs to promote ISF system in the target areas and develop budgetary plan for the application and practicability of the operation and maintenance plans, such trainings   should be conducted for  10 existing WUAs, in Kunduz, Chardara, Qalai Zal and Alia bad districts of Kunduz province and Baghlan Jadid, Pole Khumri and Nuhreen districts of Baghlan province. \r\n\r\nIt is worth mentioning that after delivering this training two follow up meetings will be conducted individually with each of the WUA ( Head, Treasurer, Secretory & Mirab) one follow up meeting will be held in December,2015 and the second will be held in January-2016,to bring in practice the delivered topic a full day practical work will be carried out with them to ensure their complete understanding and ability to promote irrigation service fee apprach and prepare budget plan for the coming year. To make sure that  there is a visit form developed by program team based on the requirement of donor to be filled in  during the follow up meeting and approved by the representative of WUA as evidence ( Minutes)and will be submitted with Bi-Monthly report to  donor \r\n','','','2015-11-30 10:28:16','2015-11-30 10:28:16',NULL,NULL,NULL,26,NULL,NULL,10,168,3,NULL,10,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','60 AFN','2015-11-28',75376.20,84376.20,'',NULL),(253,NULL,'Variety Selection Training to Farmers-Through Association ','32550A084','','1.1.1 Training Farmers through Associations','','8500','32550L711','',0,'','The anticipated outcomes and impacts of this project would be explained as following: \r\nThe participated farmers will know the Ag-Varieties and its importance.\r\nThe variety Selection skills of participated farmers will be improved and will be able to select appropriate varieties of watermelon and grapes and produce quality and quantity licit crops.\r\nThe volume of the productions of participants would be increased.\r\nThe prices of the productions of the participants would be going up.','2015-10-28 07:00:00','2015-11-12 08:00:00','','','','','',2400.80,2400.80,NULL,'2015-10-28 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','Based on SAGAL work plan this 1 day training program is planned as TOF. And 200 farmers will be trained through (Bost Fruits & Vegetable Productive & Commercial Association- BF&VP&CA). The stated association will be responsible to provide the beneficiaries list and introduce 200 farmers, coordinate the training with Hilmand DAIL, find out training venue with all requirements and invite the participants to the training program. SAGAL Hilmand team will be responsible to provide financial support, facilitate liaison between (BF&VP&CA), relevant departments and appointed trainer, and similarly other tasks including but not limited to collecting of beneficiaries list, writing of PA+BOQ, financial documen