'','Aileu is one of pre-selected districts to be targeted by the expansion of ESS nation-wide. Manatuto is rural district with majority (more than 90%) of its population relies on farming as livelihood and source of food. The workshop is done to increase awareness of the stakeholders to the program objectives and activities and to develop collaborative efforts and action plan accordingly.','','','2015-12-09 07:58:06','2015-12-09 07:58:06',57,57,NULL,85,NULL,72,30,252,35,57,7,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,0.00,200.00,'',NULL),(544,NULL,'Pistachio Exposure Visit for 115 lead farmers to Helmandi Farm Daman  ','32717A007 ','',': 2.1.1.4  # of lead farmers participated in the exposure visit - pistachio value chain','','8500/8530/8420','32717L007','',0,'','Pistachio is a high value perennial horticulture crop. Pistachio trees grow wild in Afghanistan and are wild-harvested for sale to local market. In 2003 pistachio Peter (male) and Carmen (female) varieties were tested for adaptation in Afghanistan. In year 2008 the pistachio verities Peter and Carmen were domesticated for orchard establishment in Kandahar province. Pistachio orchard was first established in Hamid Helmandi Research Farm (HRF) located in Damaan district, Kandahar which has shown well adaptability around Kandahar climatic condition. The pistachio orchard established in Helmandi Research Farm did produce a nominal yield comparing to wild varieties which were grown in Badghis, Herat, Balkh, Badakhshan and Takhar. \r\n\r\nPistachio trees are broad, bushy, and 8-10 m tall. Buds form in early spring and pollen is released in early to mid-April. Nuts may be harvested from late August through September. Pistachios produce male and female flowers on separate trees and are wind pollinated. \r\n\r\nIn order to promote and extend pistachio cultivation in Kandahar, Mercy Corps HVPHDP Program will work with 240 lead farmers in (Maiwand, Arghistan, Spin Boldak, Takhtapol, Zhari and Panjwai) districts on pistachio cultivation, processing and marketing. Under the program plan, 240 pistachio orchard each 4 jerib will be established in six districts of Kandahar\r\n\r\nThe program has initially planned to  arrange pistachio exposure for 115 lead farmers of selected districts. This specific exposure is planning to take place in Helmandi Pistachio Farm located in Daman district of Kandahar in close coordination with DAIL Kandahar. Helmandi Pistachio Farm is the only entity in Afghanistan working in improved variety of Pistachio in Kandahar since 2002. Helmandi farm as model nursery and pistachio orchard is a model for Afghanistan. \r\nThis exposure visit is intended to increase practical understandability of 115 farmers in basic pistachio cultivation practices and understanding techniques which will allow them to replicate learnt knowledge more effectively in their own expected orchard in all six districts of Kandahar.\r\n','2015-12-15 08:00:00','2016-03-15 07:00:00','','','','','',2627.72,2627.72,NULL,'2015-12-06 08:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'in progress',NULL,'','','','As mentioned 115 lead farmers are expected to participate in pistachio exposure visit.','','','2015-12-13 06:09:26','2015-12-13 06:09:26',NULL,NULL,NULL,104,NULL,NULL,5,167,37,104,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','60','2015-12-06',157662.00,157662.00,'',NULL),(545,NULL,'PMSD (Multi Stakeholders Meeting) – Vegetable Value Chain (follow up the previous PMSD meeting','32550A085','','2.1.1  Value Chain Analyses','','8500','32550L721','',0,'','1.	The stakeholders in the market system/ value chain will be able to identify gaps in the entire value chains and look for appropriate solutions either through engaging with themselves in small groups or seeking support from relevant other stakeholders.\r\n2.	The stakeholders engaged in the chain will start to find meaning in taking the issues confronting the value chain/ma