plore facts, issues and possible solutions properly, conflict can often be resolved effectively.\r\nThis conflict resolution course:\r\n1.	Provide participants with tools to identify positions, points of disagreement, and causes of conflict.\r\n2.	Give participants suggestions for adapting to various communication styles.\r\n3.	Introduce several proven strategies to enhance listening skills.\r\n4.	Furnish multiple suggestions for addressing common workplace challenges.\r\nThere will be a linkage between CDCs members and they will cooperate and coordinate between together in the next future.\r\n','2015-05-06 07:00:00','2015-05-30 07:00:00','','','','','',599.00,539.00,NULL,'2015-05-04 07:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,'','','','I.	JUSTIFICATION\r\nThe conflict resolution training will inform the CDCs members about what the Conflict Resolution system in Afghanistan and how they can find the problem root and find it a suitable solution. Also after identifying the problem how they can share with local government and what is responsibility the local government about conflict and problems solving.\r\nThey will also link to each other communities’ shura’s. And deliver the copied messages to other community members\r\n.\r\n','','','2015-12-10 05:54:48','2015-12-10 05:54:48',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,10,4,67,3,NULL,11,'','','','',0,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','1$=AFN 55','2015-05-04',29645.00,32945.00,'',NULL),(565,NULL,'Support – Private Sector (Vegetable Trader) – through inputs','32550A127','','1.2.3 Promote market and input services  ','','8500','32550L715','',0,'','Mr. Rahim khan is vegetable trader and internal exporter, he has been purchasing vegetable (Tomato, Green bean, Okra, Zucchini, Cucumber, Onion, Potato, Paper and watermelon) and export to other provinces (Kunar, Laghman, Gardiz, Kabul, Lugar and khost) of Afghanistan. If MCA-SAGAL arrange linkage meeting between farmers and trader (Rahim khan) and support him thr